msgid "/broh´k\\@t/, /broh´ket\\`/, n\\."
msgstr "/broh´k\\@t/, /broh´ket\\`/, 名詞"

#: ../../B/broket.rst:9
msgid ""
"[rare; by analogy with ‘bracket’: a ‘broken bracket’] Either of the "
"characters ``<`` and ``>``\\, when used as paired enclosing delimiters. This"
" word originated as a contraction of the phrase ‘broken bracket’, that is, a"
" bracket that is bent in the middle. (At MIT, and apparently in the "
":ref:`Real-World` as well, these are usually called :ref:`angle-"
"brackets`\\.)"
msgstr ""
"[まれ。‘bracket’との類推から。‘壊れた括弧(broken bracket)’]対にして囲む区切り記号として使われるときの ``<`` と "
"``>`` の文字のいずれか。この語は‘broken "
"bracket’、すなわち真ん中で折れ曲がった括弧、という句の短縮として生まれた。(MITでは、そしてどうやら\\ :ref:`Real-"
"World`\\ でも、これらはたいてい\\ :ref:`angle-brackets`\\ と呼ばれる。)"
